title: UChicago's Rajan: Chance of One Fed Cut in 2026
description: Raghuram Rajan, University of Chicago professor and former IMF chief economist, says the economy has held up well and has strong momentum entering the year, with tax cuts expected early on. He speaks with Katie Greifeld and Romaine Bostick on “The Close.” (Source: Bloomberg)
